{"lemma":"نادِراً","slug":"نادِراً","root":"ن.د.ر","root_slug":"ن-د-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-د-ر","pos":"ADV","pos_camel":"adv","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39612"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%8B"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rare, extraordinary"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"strange, unusual"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"excellent, priceless, eminent, precious"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"eccentric"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of نَدَرَ (nadara, “to be rare”) and نَدُرَ (nadura, “to be strange”). Compare Hebrew נדיר (nadír, “rare”)."},"ipa":["/naː.dir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39612","headword_ar":"نَادِرٌ","root":"ndr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara","text_ar":"نَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Falling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming, out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, from another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see 1]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wild ass going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming, forth from the mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prominence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"projecting part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a mountain. (A, * Msb.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What remains here and there upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of rain, i. e., of rain-water: n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. of the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAdiru","text_ar":"نَوَادِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribati AlA_ibilu mino naAdiri","text_ar":"شَرِبَتِ الاـِبِلُ مِنْ نَادِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaTari","text_ar":"المَطَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAdirihi","text_ar":"نَوَادِرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels drank of what remained here and there upon the ground, of the water of the rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Extraordinary; strange; rare; unusual;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to speech or language [and to a word and any other thing: fem. and n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. of the latter as above: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara","text_ar":"نَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadura","text_ar":"نَدُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very extraordinary, strange, rare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unusual,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to speech or language; and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAdirapN","text_ar":"نَادِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates] applied to a word: pl. of the latter as above: (Mz, 13th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawoE","text_ar":"نَوْع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muT~aridN","text_ar":"مُطَّرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAdiru AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"نَوَادِرُ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what deviate from the generality of words"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, K.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN naAdirapu Alz~amaAni","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ نَادِرَةُ الزَّمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the unequalled of the age."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAdirapN","text_ar":"نَادِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", used in this manner as a subst., signifies (tropical:)  Any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinary, strange, rare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unusual, thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above.] See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDoHikaAtN","text_ar":"مُضْحِكَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yakuwnu *`lika A_il~aA naAdirFA","text_ar":"لَا يَكُونُ ذٰلِكَ اـِلَّا نَادِرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadorapN","text_ar":"نَدْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["A"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"نادر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23791#018b5d","body_html":"<span>النادر: ما قل وجوده وإن لم يخالف القياس.</span>"}]}}